cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV

This paper proposes a novel method for reinforcement learning in sparse reward environments. It is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves deep learning and policy optimization. It also involves exploration and competition between agents, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The tasks evaluated in the paper involve manipulating objects with a robotic arm, which further supports the inclusion of cs.RO. Finally, the paper includes visual inputs and image processing, which could also place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
